Beginning Thursday Sept. 9 2021 until Memorial Day 2022: The US 197 - Dalles Bridge will be fully closed between Washington and Oregon from 8 p.m. Thursday nights through 6 a.m. Monday mornings for bridge deck replacement work. Note: During the full weekend bridge closures travelers will follow a signed detour using the US 97 Biggs Junction Bridge. These closures will occur every weekend until Memorial Day 2022. Note: Currently travelers can expect to see delays of up to 20 minutes weeknights from 8 p.m. Monday to 6 a.m. Thursday due to single lane closures. During these times traffic will be controlled by flaggers.This work is being performed by ODOT. For more information contact Kacey Davey (Kacey.L.Davey@odot.state.or.us) at 541-280-2716 For project information visit: https://www.oregon.gov/odot/projects/pages/project-details.aspx?project=20442
